        <h2>Bed Leveling Techniques</h2>
        <p>Bed leveling ensures the print bed is parallel to the extruder nozzle. Use a 3D printer's built-in probe or manual calibration:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Place the printer on a flat surface and turn it on.</li>
            <li>Use the 'level bed' function in your slicer software (e.g., Pronterface, Cura).</li>
            <li>Adjust the Z-axis height until the nozzle just touches the bed.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Nozzle Offset Calibration</h2>
        <p>The nozzle offset determines how far the extruder moves from the bed. To calibrate:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Print a calibration cube with known dimensions.</li>
            <li>Measure the cube's size and adjust the offset in your slicer settings.</li>
            <li>Repeat until prints are accurate.</li>
        </ul>
