    <section>
        <h2>Step-by-Step Filament Change Process</h2>
        <p>Follow these steps to change filament without damaging your printer:</p>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Prepare the New Filament:</strong> Load the new filament into the extruder and heat the nozzle to 190°C–230°C.</li>
            <li><strong>Clear Old Filament:</strong> Move the nozzle slowly over the previous filament to remove residue.</li>
            <li><strong>Check for Clogs:</strong> Use a needle or cleaning tool to clear any blockages in the extruder and tubes.</li>
            <li><strong>Calibrate for New Material:</strong> Adjust print settings (e.g., flow rate, temperature) according to the new filament type.</li>
            <li><strong>Test Print:</strong> Create a small test object to ensure consistent extrusion and adhesion.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Common Issues After Filament Change</h2>
        <p>If you experience under-extrusion or poor print quality, check the following:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Ensure the nozzle is properly heated and aligned.</li>
            <li>Verify that the filament is correctly loaded and not tangled.</li>
            <li>Check for any obstructions in the extruder or tubes.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
